<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="147" type="sexual morph">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Sexual morph.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="147">
Stromata scattered to grouped, pulvinate, circular to elliptical in outline, elevated beyond bark surface forming pustules, 0.6-0.7 mm high, 0.9-1.0 mm diam., dark brown to black. Ascomata perithecial, subglobose to ampulliform, 4-8 grouped, 700-780 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high, 220-280 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam., immersed in stromata. Ascomatal wall 17-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of 7-10 layers of polygonal, 4-6.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, dark brown cells. Ostiolar neck central, cylindrical, 400-430 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 100-110 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, periphysate. Paraphyses septate, unbranched, cylindrical, 92.5-110 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 3.5-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide. Asci unitunicate, cylindrical, 110-175 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9-12.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(av. 145.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 15), broadly rounded at the apex, with a pronounced non-amyloid apical annulus, pedicellate (12.5-27.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long), with 8 ascospores. Ascospores fusiform to ellipsoid, smooth, brown, with 3 transverse and 0-2 oblique or vertical septa, 13.5-18 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(av. 15.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 50), l/w 1.7-2.6 (av. 2.1, n = 50).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="147" type="asexual morph (nature)">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Asexual morph (nature).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="147">
Conidiomata pycnidial, globose to subglobose, grouped, 220-300 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high, 90-150 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam., immersed in stromata. Conidiomatal wall 8-18 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of 3-5 layers of polygonal, 3-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, dark brown cells. Ostiolar neck central, cylindrical, 80-110 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 90-110 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, composed of polygonal cells, periphysate. Conidiophores hyaline, thin-walled, with branches bearing a group of 2-5 phialides terminally. Phialides tapering toward the tip, hyaline, 11-16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Conidia ellipsoidal, with a slightly apiculate base, hyaline, smooth-walled, 3-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(av. 3.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 50). Chlamydospores not observed.
</paragraph>
